name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: Daft physics playground GOAT SIMULATOR is the lowest form of wit. By Andy Kelly

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: If Goat Simulator really was a goat simulator, you'd spend the whole game padding around a field eating grass and occasionally being milked, before ending up on a plate in some upmarket restaurant. But that would make for a rubbish game, so instead Coffee Stain Studios, the Swedish team behind the Sanctum series, have used artistic licence.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: You crash around a physics-enabled world knocking things over, headbutting people, dragging stuff around with your tongue, and generally being a pain in arse for points. Think Tony Hawk's Pro Skater, but with a goat.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: I timed it, and it took me 23 minutes to get bored. The single map is tiny, and although loaded with stuff to mess around with, your interaction is limited. You can headbutt things, or kick them with your hind legs if you hold back while attacking.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: You can lick things with your tongue, which functions a bit like a bendier version of Just Cause's tether cable. And you can jump and spin around in the air. That's pretty much it when you're a goat, and by combining these actions you score points and rack up combos.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: Destroying things in quick succession, staying in the air for extended periods of time, and other goat-based mischief sends your score ticking up, as do other more specific actions. Terrorise a group of people having a barbecue in a backyard and you get the Party Crasher bonus. Crush a car with a giant boulder and you get Dodge This.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: Charge through Coffee Stain's office and you earn a Goat Among Legends bonus. Discovering these is where I had the most fun with the game, but the limited map size means you'll probably uncover all the secrets and Easter eggs in an hour.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: Like Octodad, Goat Simulator is a joke stretched way too thin. Humour is subjective, of course. You might chuckle yourself unconscious when you play it, but I didn't laugh at all. Not even a sharp exhalation through the nose. There was a time when ragdoll physics was funny, but the novelty has worn off for me.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: Goat Simulator's success is down to it being the perfect word-of-mouth game. You watch someone sniggering at it on YouTube and you want to buy it to be in on the joke. But beyond the eye-catching premise, it's just a bad, amateurish and boring game.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: It perhaps seems mean-spirited to give a silly comedy game from a small studio a kicking like this, but Coffee Stain don't get a free ride just because they're indie. They're charging actual money for this, remember. Too much money.

name: Emelia_Kaylee
message: They know it sucks. "You should probably spend your money on something else," they advise, wisely. But no one cares, do they? As I type this, it's the best-selling game on Steam.
